Yes it can be activated by Telephone. 
- Insert the Serial 
- Select the Activation by telephone
- Call Microsoft by the given number
- Select activate a Microsoft Software
- Insert (when asked to) the numbers that are on the screen
- Insert on your computer, the numbers that the robot gave to you

The "retail version" comes with only 1 serial number, and Microsoft only allows 1 serial number per computer.

The "volume licensing version" allows multiple computers using the same serial number.  However, every 180 days you would need to rearm the sh*t, and you can only rearm it at the max of 3 times.

So when somebody claims they have an activator for Office 2010, they are basically lying.  So far, there is no permanent activation for this product.
